lies play a key role in human development. Based on present-day energy supply technology, our knowledge of available resources and the development of new forms of energy, the study develops an assessment of future energy supplies. It takes account of both the economic and - above all - the ethical dimensions involved. Key Features topical issue with potentially explosive political and economic consequences comprehensive multi-facetted and multidisciplinary approaches to solutions  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEnvironmental economics. 0aEnvironmental engineering. 4aEnergieversorgung. 4aEthik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aGethmann, Carl Friedrich, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHeinloth, Klaus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRumpff, Klaus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWitt, Andreas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE UND GESCHICHTE 2008z9783110209426oZDB-23-DGE0 cprintz978311018431040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311019372540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110193725423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110193725/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGEb2008  aZDB-23-DGGb2008  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014